Build an OS X nip2.app with jhbuild

See:

	http://www.vips.ecs.soton.ac.uk/index.php?title=Build_on_OS_X

Steps:

1) install gtk-osx

	https://live.gnome.org/GTK+/OSX/Building

2) jhbuild bootstrap

3) jhbuild build meta-gtk-osx-bootstrap

4) jhbuild build meta-gtk-osx-core

5) append 

	moduleset = "file:///Users/john/GIT/build-osx/7.30/vips-osx.modules"

   to ~/.jhbuildrc-custom

6) edit vips-osx.modules to update versions and paths

7) jhbuild build nip2

8) jhbuild run nip2 to test the build

9) install the bundler:

	   https://live.gnome.org/GTK%2B/OSX/Bundling

10) ./package-nip2.sh

   will generate ~/Desktop/nip2-x.x.x.dmg, using the binary in ~/gtk/inst


